Author: Andi Lucena Rausch
Content:
Most people need a high dose of melatonin. And, there is no known dose that can cause damage or kill you.  

In fact, NIH has an abstract where they found HIGH DOSE Melatonin combined with antivenom counters oxidative stress from snakebites, that CAN kill.

In other words MELATONIN helps heal.

https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/28089603/

Author: Katalin Hum
Content:
Just fix your circadian rhythm.
Stop looking at your phone after dark, get rid off LED (blue) lights in your house. Go to bed early, wake up with a Sun and go outside instead of reaching your phone first.

Author: Sarah St Cyr
Content: Good Morning Anthony! Thankyou! Your Hearts So Good To keep sharing this info in a way everyone could have access to it As long as we keep sharing it with others but even then not everyones food choice rights are respected or supported and sometimes people still struggle even when they do have those rights to make good food choices all the time for themselves. Everyone has that struggle when our lives effect eachothers! Its Universal! We are all in this together and if not it has consequences down the road and some take advantage of that or take advantage of our vulnerabilities especially when chronically ill and try to take food & healing rights away for everyone save for a chosen few! Why the chosen concept never fully sat right with me and if one is there is a responsibility that comes with it to lead others to good with it as we are able to along with our own struggles. Sometimes those struggles overtake or are so detrimentally overstimulating that we cant for certain time periods but then when we can handle more we do what we can in good conscience. Brain Fog sure does make this difficult. Sure am glad when we are blessed and others are to have the foods and melatonin we need to heal ourselves and heal & protect others same with prayer food!

Author: Petra Zellars-Crawford
Content:
20–30 minutes of morning sunlight exposure (preferably within an hour of waking up) is usually enough to help anchor your circadian rhythm and support healthy melatonin production at night.
The more consistent your exposure to natural daylight (especially in the morning), the better your melatonin cycle will function

Author: Elisa Novick
Content:
I have a big problem with taking melatonin. At any dosage it gives me the more horrific nightmares that I cannot wake from. They don't even feel like mine; I don't have nightmares like these. I've read that others have this problem too. And I know people who don't have any problem with it.

Also, when I was studying, I was taught that if you take it, your body will stop making it. I don't know if that is true. I tend to believe AW, but since I can't take it, I have no way of knowing.
